"{\"uid\": \"express.co.uk-sport-othersport-1927647-Paris-Olympics-2024-tom-daley-speaks-out-partner\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  Tom Daley claims he could not have a better partner as he prepares to take a primetime cruise down the River Seine in Friday night's Olympic opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 160, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2, \"end\": 11, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0220535062370349e-41, \"text\": \"Tom Daley\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\"}, {\"begin\": 105, \"end\": 116, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Daley and rower Helen Glover will carry the British flag as the Games get under way under the shadow of Paris' world-famous postcard landmarks.\", \"from\": 162, \"to\": 305, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 178, \"end\": 190, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\", \"score\": 0.9968858553495725, \"rank\": 0.0031234382808593376, \"text\": \"Helen Glover\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\"}, {\"begin\": 206, \"end\": 218, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Jack\", \"score\": 0.9986137425275965, \"rank\": 0.0013881801327423077, \"text\": \"British flag\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Jack\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Jack\"}, {\"begin\": 266, \"end\": 271, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999998008207, \"rank\": 1.9924130631986554e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Daley, with one gold and three bronzes from five Olympics, and Glover, a two-time gold medallist from three appearances, were popular choices to lead in Team GB.\", \"from\": 307, \"to\": 468, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 370, \"end\": 376, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Glover\", \"score\": 0.9999999232213698, \"rank\": 7.674589723681878e-08, \"text\": \"Glover\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Glover\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Glover\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Pick up your ultimate guide to the Olympics!\", \"from\": 470, \"to\": 514, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Going for Gold provides the day-by-day rundown of what's on and when.\", \"from\": 515, \"to\": 584, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Clickhereto buy.\", \"from\": 585, \"to\": 601, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Daley is the first diver to get the honour and Glover the first woman rower, following Olympic icons Sir Steve Redgrave and Sir Matthew Pinsent.\", \"from\": 603, \"to\": 747, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 650, \"end\": 656, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Glover\", \"score\": 0.9999999232213698, \"rank\": 7.674589723681878e-08, \"text\": \"Glover\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Glover\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Glover\"}, {\"begin\": 704, \"end\": 722, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Redgrave\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sir Steve Redgrave\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Redgrave\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Redgrave\"}, {\"begin\": 731, \"end\": 746, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Pinsent\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matthew Pinsent\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Pinsent\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Pinsent\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was sworn to secrecy, I was told two days ago.\", \"from\": 749, \"to\": 798, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The first person I called was my husband Lance, because I wanted to tell him,\\\"\\u00a0said Daley, who will join theDiscovery+commentary team after competing in the 10m synchro event next Monday.\", \"from\": 799, \"to\": 986, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It has been really tough, we moved to America and then I decided I wanted to go back to training, and it has been hard with the travel.\", \"from\": 988, \"to\": 1124, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It has been a real journey.\", \"from\": 1126, \"to\": 1154, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I feel really proud to have committed to going on another Olympic journey, against all odds.\", \"from\": 1155, \"to\": 1247, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I really went for it, and he was so happy for me.\", \"from\": 1248, \"to\": 1297, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Discovery+is the new home of the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1299, \"to\": 1341, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The streamer is set to broadcast 3,800 hours of sport live from Paris.\", \"from\": 1342, \"to\": 1412, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1406, \"end\": 1411, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999998008207, \"rank\": 1.9924130631986554e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sports fans can getDiscovery+ for \\u00a33.99a month until the end of 2024 via Amazon Prime's video channels.\", \"from\": 1414, \"to\": 1517, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1487, \"end\": 1499, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amazon_Prime\", \"score\": 0.9997497647079302, \"rank\": 0.0002502962467144605, \"text\": \"Amazon Prime\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amazon_Prime\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amazon_Prime\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This also comes with anAmazon Prime 30-day free trial.\", \"from\": 1518, \"to\": 1572, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"My youngest son [Phoenix] will not remember but Robbie, who has just turned six, is going to.\", \"from\": 1574, \"to\": 1668, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1592, \"end\": 1599, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phoenix_Raceway\", \"score\": 0.9563649456774675, \"rank\": 0.04551995382044847, \"text\": \"Phoenix\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phoenix_Raceway\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phoenix_Raceway\"}, {\"begin\": 1623, \"end\": 1629, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Donnachaidh\", \"score\": 0.9822476629991398, \"rank\": 0.018067846384287475, \"text\": \"Robbie\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Donnachaidh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Donnachaidh\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He is very excited; he has been learning a lot about the Olympics at school and it is going to be really special to look back at photos and say they were there.\", \"from\": 1669, \"to\": 1829, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am looking forward to sharing the moment with Helen too, she is such an inspiration.\\\"\", \"from\": 1831, \"to\": 1919, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At different points in this Olympic cycle, it's fair to say that both Daley and Glover were uncertain to be in Paris.\", \"from\": 1921, \"to\": 2038, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2001, \"end\": 2007, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Glover\", \"score\": 0.9999999232213698, \"rank\": 7.674589723681878e-08, \"text\": \"Glover\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Glover\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Glover\"}, {\"begin\": 2032, \"end\": 2037, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999998008207, \"rank\": 1.9924130631986554e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Glover retired after the Rio Games but had a change of heart during the pandemic, returning to the sport to become the first mother to row for Team GB.\", \"from\": 2040, \"to\": 2191, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I called my husband Steve (Backshall), I think he was crying,\\\" said Glover.\", \"from\": 2193, \"to\": 2269, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2262, \"end\": 2268, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Glover\", \"score\": 0.9999999232213698, \"rank\": 7.674589723681878e-08, \"text\": \"Glover\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Glover\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Glover\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I called my Mum who definitely cried.\", \"from\": 2270, \"to\": 2308, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I have not spoken to my Dad yet.\", \"from\": 2309, \"to\": 2341, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's a pinch-me moment, because I had four years out of the sport.\", \"from\": 2343, \"to\": 2410, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"From Rio to Tokyo, I had retired.\", \"from\": 2411, \"to\": 2444, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2416, \"end\": 2419, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9932075957175706, \"rank\": 0.0068388565611973975, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If it wasn't for that ambition to come back and to prove people wrong, and to do it with kids, I'd be watching on television.\", \"from\": 2446, \"to\": 2572, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Imagine if you'd told me in the middle of Covid when I had two newborn twins and a toddler, that if I did all of this, I'd be leading out the team as a flagbearer?\", \"from\": 2574, \"to\": 2738, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I just feel like it's something I would never have believed.\\\"\", \"from\": 2739, \"to\": 2800, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Watch every moment of the Olympic GamesParis 2024live only ondiscovery+, the streaming home of the Olympics.\", \"from\": 2802, \"to\": 2910, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We use your sign-up to provide content in ways you have consented to and to improve our understanding of you.\", \"from\": 2912, \"to\": 3021, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This may include adverts from us and 3rd parties based on our understanding.\", \"from\": 3022, \"to\": 3098, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You can unsubscribe at any time.\", \"from\": 3099, \"to\": 3131, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy Policy    SEARCH  CONNECT WITH US  TODAY'S PAPER  See today's front and back pages, download the newspaper, order back issues and use the historic Daily Express newspaper archive.\", \"from\": 3132, \"to\": 3327, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3295, \"end\": 3308, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2321056314262595e-20, \"text\": \"Daily Express\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"EXPRESS.CO.UK  Daily Express uses notifications to keep you updated\", \"from\": 3329, \"to\": 3396, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3344, \"end\": 3357, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\